expect: Lanes with explicit next_step+artifact fields have lower rework rate; identify minimal handoff contract from lane history

method.approach: Analyzed all SWARM-LANES.md entries (n=33 closed lanes: 31 MERGED + 2 ABANDONED). Classified into clean-close vs rework/correction-lag cases. Measured metadata field presence for each category.

rework_cases.cause: Redundant open — concurrent session already completed F-EXP10. anti-repeat T3 check missing.
Redundant open — DOMEX-HLP2-S346 already completed orient.py stall detection.
actual=TBD effectively — no artifact produced, experiment confounded.
Priority shift — lane opened but never executed. No successor named, no handoff.
Stale 4+ sessions — no execution. No successor named at ABANDONED close.

artifact_path_declared.rework_rate: 3/5 had path declared but file missing
artifact_path_declared.verdict: Necessary but not sufficient — artifact must also exist on disk

actual_outcome_filled.rework_rate: 0/5 rework cases had actual filled at close
actual_outcome_filled.verdict: STRONGEST PREDICTOR: actual=TBD at session boundary = 100% rework rate

successor_named_or_next_step_none.verdict: Required for continuation lanes — prevents 4+ session lag

next_step_during_work.verdict: NOT discriminative (confirmed F-HLP1 finding) — 0/29 predictive in prior analysis

at_open: artifact=<specific-path> (not TBD — commit to deliverable before working)
at_close: actual=<outcome> (fill EAD loop — never close with TBD)
EITHER: next_step=none (terminal) OR successor=<lane-id> in Notes (continuation)
anti_redundancy: T3 check: run git log before opening lane to verify concurrent sessions haven't closed same work

predicted_vs_actual.predicted: next_step+artifact fields would be top predictors of clean handoff
predicted_vs_actual.actual: actual=TBD is the single strongest rework predictor (100% precision). next_step during work is not discriminative (F-HLP1 confirmed). artifact path alone is insufficient — file must exist on disk.
predicted_vs_actual.diff: Expected next_step to matter; it doesn't. actual=outcome filling is the real gate. Successor naming at close (not during work) prevents 4+ session lag.
